2026-05-17 05:28:21 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #14 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"intent": "Compute Pearson correlation between 3-day rainfall and estimated Enterococcus for Boston Harbor beaches located in >90% EJ communities, using 2023 records and tag rules (<x=>x/2, >x=>x).", "code": "import pandas as pd, numpy as np, re\n\n# Load Boston Harbor beach list\nwith open('kramabench-environment-hard-10/files/boston-harbor-beaches.txt','r') as f:\n    beaches=[line.strip() for line in f if line.strip()]\nbeaches=set(beaches)\n\n# Load EJ populations and identify municipalities with >90% EJ BG population share\nEJ=pd.read_csv('kramabench-environment-hard-10/files/environmental-justice-populations.csv')\nEJ['Percent of population in EJ BGs']=pd.to_numeric(EJ['Percent of population in EJ BGs'], errors='coerce')\nEJ_munis=set(EJ.loc[EJ['Percent of population in EJ BGs']>90,'Municipality'].astype(str).str.strip())\n\n# Helper to parse beach city from first column header cell like: \"M Street Beach, South Boston: Bacterial Water Quality\"\ndef get_beach_municipality(col0):\n    if pd.isna(col0):\n        return None\n    s=str(col0)\n    # after comma, before ': Bacterial'\n    # e.g., 'M Street Beach, South Boston: Bacterial Water Quality'\n    m=re.search(r',\\s*([^:]+):', s)\n    if m:\n        return m.group(1).strip()\n    return None\n\n# Load relevant datasheets\nfiles=[\n 'kramabench-environment-hard-8/files/m_street_beach_datasheet.csv',\n 'kramabench-environment-hard-8/files/tenean_beach_datasheet.csv',\n 'kramabench-environment-hard-8/files/wollaston_beach_datasheet.csv',\n]\n# note: Pleasure Bay/ Castle Island not downloaded; but they are Boston Harbor list too. Let's also add from hard-11 if exists in sandbox? not downloaded. We'll proceed with these three only.\n\nrows=[]\nfor fp in files:\n    df=pd.read_csv(fp, header=2)\n    # Rename columns if messy\n    # Expect columns: Date,1-Day Rain,2